A minute has 60 seconds, of course. So the minutes can be calculated by an (integral division:

```java
int min = time / 60;
``` 

The seconds are the remainder of a division of `time` by 60. The remainder can be get by the modulo operator (`%`):

```java
int sec = time % 60;
``` 

Use [`nf()`](https://processing.org/reference/nf_.html) to convert an integral value to a string with leading zeros:

```java
int min = time / 60;
int sec = time % 60;
text(nf(min, 1) + &quot;:&quot; + nf(sec, 2), 1025, 60);
```

